## Pre-existing Tests Status

All 1868 previously-passing tests continue to pass. The +15 new tests that pass immediately
are the PROP-019 exhaustiveness tests in `step2-scan-vault.test.ts` — these are Tier-0
type-level tests that pass because `HydrationFailureReason` in `shared/snapshots.ts` already
includes all 5 values (`'yaml-parse' | 'missing-field' | 'invalid-value' | 'block-parse' | 'unknown'`)
from the block-based migration. The runtime assertions (which reason produces each value)
also pass because we're just asserting type members, not implementation routing.

---

## What Phase 2b Must Implement

To make all 23 failing tests (and 1 module-error file) pass, Phase 2b must:

1. **`capture-auto-save/parse-markdown-to-blocks.ts`** — Replace module-level counter with
   per-call positional BlockId allocation (`block-0`, `block-1`, ... reset per invocation).
   This fixes PROP-025 (7 tests).

2. **`app-startup/scan-vault.ts`** — Add `parseMarkdownToBlocks` to `ScanVaultPorts`;
   call it after `parseNote` in the per-file loop; fold `Err(BlockParseError)` and `Ok([])`
   to `{kind:'hydrate', reason:'block-parse'}`; wrap the per-file parse block in try-catch
   to catch parser exceptions and fold to `{kind:'hydrate', reason:'unknown', detail:<message>}`;
   fold unrecognised `Result.Err` variants to `reason:'unknown'` as well.
   This fixes PROP-026 (5 tests), PROP-029 (2 tests), PROP-028 (4 tests), PROP-030 partial (Step 2).

3. **`app-startup/hydrate-note.ts`** (new file) — Implement `hydrateNote(snapshot)` as a pure
   function: `parseMarkdownToBlocks(snapshot.body)` + `Note.fromSnapshot(snapshot, blocks)`.
   Export `hydrateNote` from this module.
   This fixes PROP-027 (12 tests, module-error file).

4. **`app-startup/hydrate-feed.ts`** — Import and call `hydrateNote` per snapshot in the
   `hydrateFeed` function to materialize `Note` aggregates. This keeps hydrateFeed pure
   (since hydrateNote is pure). Update return value to include `noteRefs` from successfully
   hydrated snapshots; add HydrationFailureReason-based corruptedFiles from Step 3 hydration.
   This fixes PROP-030 partial (Step 3 counting tests).

5. **`app-startup/scan-vault.ts` — `ScanVaultPorts` type** — Add `parseMarkdownToBlocks` field
   (type: `(markdown: string) => Result<ReadonlyArray<Block>, BlockParseError>`).
   The field is pure; it is a port only in the structural sense that it is injected.

